<figureCitation box="[1270,1395,506,532]" captionStart-0="Fig. 14" captionStart-1="Fig. 15" captionStart-2="Fig. 16" captionStart-3="Fig. 17" captionStartId-0="31.[189,232,1066,1092]" captionStartId-1="31.[189,232,1999,2025]" captionStartId-2="32.[189,232,1064,1090]" captionStartId-3="32.[189,232,1997,2023]" captionTargetBox-0="[189,1397,266,1024]" captionTargetBox-1="[191,1400,1194,1962]" captionTargetBox-2="[189,1398,261,1023]" captionTargetBox-3="[189,1398,1195,1959]" captionTargetId-0="figure@31.[189,1398,265,1024]" captionTargetId-1="figure@31.[191,1400,1194,1962]" captionTargetId-2="figure@32.[189,1398,261,1023]" captionTargetId-3="figure@32.[189,1398,1195,1959]" captionTargetPageId-0="31" captionTargetPageId-1="31" captionTargetPageId-2="32" captionTargetPageId-3="32" captionText-0="Fig. 14. Distribution map of Trichomyrmex abyssinicus (Forel, 1894 a), T. almosayari sp. nov., T. chobauti (Emery, 1897), T. lameerei (Forel, 1902) and T. shakeri sp. nov." captionText-1="Fig. 15. Distribution map of Trichomyrmex destructor (Jerdon, 1851)." captionText-2="Fig. 16. Distribution map of Trichomyrmex mayri (Forel, 1902)." captionText-3="Fig. 17. Distribution map of Trichomyrmex perplexus (Radchenko, 1997) and T. robustior (Forel, 1892)." httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/193059/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/193060/files/figure.png" httpUri-2="https://zenodo.org/record/193061/files/figure.png" httpUri-3="https://zenodo.org/record/193062/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Figs 14â€“17</figureCitation>
